{"attribution":"Occupational Safety and Health Administration, Protecting Workers from Slips, Trips and Falls during Disaster Response, OSHA 4301-08 2023, Chinese Simplified; no OSHA or U.S. Department of Labor endorsement or affiliation is implied.","cases":[{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"osha-disaster-falls-simplified-v1/sentence-001","input":"应急救援人员在应对自然和人为灾难时，会面临因滑倒、绊倒和跌倒而受伤甚至死亡的风险。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.osha.gov/sites/default/files/publications/OSHA4301.pdf","source_case_id":"sentence-001","split":"document"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"osha-disaster-falls-simplified-v1/sentence-002","input":"雇主必须采取的、确保工人安全的步骤包括：制定事前灾难响应方案并确保应急救援人员了解该方案。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.osha.gov/sites/default/files/publications/OSHA4301.pdf","source_case_id":"sentence-002","split":"document"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"osha-disaster-falls-simplified-v1/sentence-003","input":"评估作业场地，以确定其是否存在或可能存在危险。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.osha.gov/sites/default/files/publications/OSHA4301.pdf","source_case_id":"sentence-003","split":"document"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"osha-disaster-falls-simplified-v1/sentence-004","input":"提供防护装备以防止滑倒、绊倒和跌倒，它们包括：防滑鞋（例如橡胶鞋底）。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.osha.gov/sites/default/files/publications/OSHA4301.pdf","source_case_id":"sentence-004","split":"document"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"osha-disaster-falls-simplified-v1/sentence-005","input":"手套，工人可以牢固地抓住栏杆 / 梯子以稳定自己。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.osha.gov/sites/default/files/publications/OSHA4301.pdf","source_case_id":"sentence-005","split":"document"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"osha-disaster-falls-simplified-v1/sentence-006","input":"头部防护装置个人跌落保护培训员工们识别危险——包括需要防护装备的危险，以及如何防止受伤。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.osha.gov/sites/default/files/publications/OSHA4301.pdf","source_case_id":"sentence-006","split":"document"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"osha-disaster-falls-simplified-v1/sentence-007","input":"尽量避免在湿滑的地方行走；将湿掉的鞋底擦干。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.osha.gov/sites/default/files/publications/OSHA4301.pdf","source_case_id":"sentence-007","split":"document"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"osha-disaster-falls-simplified-v1/sentence-008","input":"使用手电筒或头盔灯，以避开洞口或地板开口、潮湿或光滑的表面、以及碎片或设备。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.osha.gov/sites/default/files/publications/OSHA4301.pdf","source_case_id":"sentence-008","split":"document"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"osha-disaster-falls-simplified-v1/sentence-009","input":"在目视检查以确保没有孔洞或薄弱处、并且可以支撑工人及其设备的重量之前，请勿踏上任何表面。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.osha.gov/sites/default/files/publications/OSHA4301.pdf","source_case_id":"sentence-009","split":"document"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"osha-disaster-falls-simplified-v1/sentence-010","input":"攀爬梯子时切勿手持设备或工具。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.osha.gov/sites/default/files/publications/OSHA4301.pdf","source_case_id":"sentence-010","split":"document"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"osha-disaster-falls-simplified-v1/sentence-011","input":"使用背包和工具带以固定设备、解放双手。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.osha.gov/sites/default/files/publications/OSHA4301.pdf","source_case_id":"sentence-011","split":"document"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"osha-disaster-falls-simplified-v1/sentence-012","input":"在高空未受保护的边缘附近移动或执行应急救援时，使用防坠落保护装置。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.osha.gov/sites/default/files/publications/OSHA4301.pdf","source_case_id":"sentence-012","split":"document"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"osha-disaster-falls-simplified-v1/sentence-013","input":"将滑倒、绊倒和跌倒的危险用通讯设备——尤其是免提设备——通知雇主/救援主管和其他工人。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.osha.gov/sites/default/files/publications/OSHA4301.pdf","source_case_id":"sentence-013","split":"document"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"osha-disaster-falls-simplified-v1/sentence-014","input":"当您对某项任务的安全性有疑问时，请停止并通知主管。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.osha.gov/sites/default/files/publications/OSHA4301.pdf","source_case_id":"sentence-014","split":"document"}}],"converter_output_used":false,"dataset":"blind-v2","id":"osha-disaster-falls-simplified-v1","input_only":true,"license":"U.S. Public Domain","modification_notice":"Extracted complete Simplified Chinese sentences from the checksum-pinned OSHA PDF, excluded the English page, URLs, phone instructions, page furniture, images, logos, and third-party content, and added input-only provenance; no expected text or converter output was used.","purpose":"candidate_source_pilot","review_policy":"domain_and_risk_must_be_assigned_from_input_only","source_class":"public_domain","stats":{"by_split":{"document":14},"eligible_pending_review":14,"exclusions":{},"raw_cases":14},"upstream_revision":"OSHA 4301-08 2023, Protecting Workers from Slips, Trips and Falls during Disaster Response, Chinese Simplified; retrieved PDF SHA-256: f2683f14e4ca64f01679e91dd43f0422e7f13721f0cf16a2c2f6cdea714079f3","version":1}
